<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="chapter-sockets">
  <title>Client-Server Applications, Networking, and Sockets</title>
  <introduction>
    <p>
     After studying this chapter, you will:
    </p>
    <objectives>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            Understand some basics about networks.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Know how to use Java's <c>URL</c> class to download network resources from a GUI or console application.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Be able to design networking applications,
            using the client/server model.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            Understand how to use Java's <c>Socket</c> and <c>ServerSocket</c> classes.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </objectives>
  </introduction>
